      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and your <strong>dried thyme </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> Marmite stock </strong>with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>pie mix</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong>, then unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until it is large enough to cover an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
